    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An app container has a public database with data that’s accessible to all users, and a private database with data that’s accessible only to the current user. A database takes requests for data and applies them to the appropriate part of the container."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You don’t create a database yourself, nor do you subclass "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "CKDatabase"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". Your app’s containers provide the databases you use to access their data. Use databases as-is to perform operations on data."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The public database is always available, regardless of whether the device has an iCloud account. When there isn’t an available iCloud account, your app can fetch records and perform queries on the public database, but it can’t create or modify records. Saving records to the public database requires an iCloud account to identify who made the changes. Access to the private database always requires an iCloud account."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The default quality of service level for database operations is "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsqualityofservice/nsqualityofservicedefault"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". For more information about quality of service, see "
                },
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "title": "Prioritize Work with Quality of Service Classes",
                  "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/Performance/Conceptual/EnergyGuide-iOS/PrioritizeWorkWithQoS.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40015243-CH39"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " in "
                },
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "title": "Energy Efficiency Guide for iOS Apps",
                  "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/Performance/Conceptual/EnergyGuide-iOS/index.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40015243"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "title": "Prioritize Work at the Task Level",
                  "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/Performance/Conceptual/power_efficiency_guidelines_osx/PrioritizeWorkAtTheTaskLevel.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40013929-CH35"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " in "
                },
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "title": "Energy Efficiency Guide for Mac Apps",
                  "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/Performance/Conceptual/power_efficiency_guidelines_osx/index.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40013929"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Note"
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Interacting with Databases",
          "anchor": "1666172"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You interact with databases as follows:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Assign a database to an operation when you want to fetch, save, delete, or query the contents of the database. The database tells the operation where to get the data. Calling the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/cloudkit/ckdatabase/1449116-addoperation"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " method of the database assigns that database to the operation implicitly."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Use a database’s convenience methods to fetch, save, delete, or query the contents of the database directly. The convenience methods act on a single item at a time."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 4,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Using Databases with Operations",
          "anchor": "1666192"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For operations that descend from the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/cloudkit/ckdatabaseoperation"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class, specify the database for executing the operation."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "If you execute operations on your own custom queue, specify the database explicitly by assigning the appropriate "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "CKDatabase"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " instance to the operation’s "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/cloudkit/ckdatabaseoperation/1515274-database"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " property."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "If you don’t use a custom queue, execute the operation using the database implicitly by calling its "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/cloudkit/ckdatabase/1449116-addoperation"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " method."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 4,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Executing Tasks Using a Database Directly",
          "anchor": "1666208"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "CKDatabase"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class offers convenience methods for accessing records, record zones, and subscriptions without using an operation. The convenience methods provide ways to fetch, save, or delete a single item asynchronously and process the results on a background thread. There is also a convenience method to search for records in the database."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Use convenience methods to rapidly prototype your app using CloudKit, with a goal of later adopting batch-processing operations and an explicit quality of service."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
